org.opentosca.toscana.core.transformation.properties

Class PropertyInstance

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.core.transformation.properties.PropertyInstance

  • public class PropertyInstance
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the instance of properties. That means that this is storing the values that get assigned to the defined properties.

        public PropertyInstance(java.util.Set<InputProperty> properties,
                        Transformation transformation)
        Creates a new property instance with no set property values for the given list (set) of properties.
        Parameters:
        properties - the set of properties to create a property instance for. Is not allowed to be null, if no props are needed add a empty set
        transformation - the related transformation. It's TransformationState will be altered by this instance according to the state of the properties
